1
00:00:02,002 --> 00:00:03,470
JIM: Previously on Gotham...

2
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:06,344
- Bruce Wayne?
- No.

3
00:00:06,507 --> 00:00:07,599
But you could be.

4
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:11,224
I've done a wonderful job
erasing the scars.

5
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:12,433
Are you prepared?

6
00:00:12,596 --> 00:00:15,145
Yes. But I still don't understand
how I can help save Gotham.

7
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:16,896
FRANK: You're only part of the plan.

8
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:20,104
You know what must happen if he refuses.

9
00:00:20,312 --> 00:00:22,531
No one refuses the Court.

10
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:24,483
- You lied to me.
- I didn't tell you the truth.

11
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:26,118
- It's the same thing!
- Perhaps.

12
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:27,996
But telling you
your mother was a con artist

13
00:00:28,111 --> 00:00:30,455
who'd only sought you out for the purposes
of getting money from me

14
00:00:30,614 --> 00:00:32,616
didn't seem like
a very attractive alternative.

15
00:00:34,326 --> 00:00:36,749
I don't love you.

16
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:38,755
You need me, Edward Nygma.

17
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:40,708
Just as I need you.

18
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:42,384
You killed Isabella.

19
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:44,218
I loved her, Oswald.

20
00:00:44,378 --> 00:00:45,379
(GUNSHOT)

21
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:12,205
- Greetings, Professor.
- Help! Somebody help!

22
00:01:12,364 --> 00:01:13,911
(GUN COCKING)

23
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,202
The building's empty.
No one's coming to help.

24
00:01:17,661 --> 00:01:18,833
Have a seat.

25
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:23,333
Who are you?

26
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:26,007
That is an excellent question.

27
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:29,681
But, I get to ask the first one.

28
00:01:32,134 --> 00:01:35,479
I can fill a room, or just one heart.

29
00:01:35,637 --> 00:01:37,560
Others may have me,
but I cannot be shared.

30
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:38,811
What am I?

31
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:41,355
What?

32
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:43,691
It's a riddle. Answer the riddle!

33
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:46,861
I... Knowledge?

34
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:51,445
Knowledge can't be shared, Professor?

35
00:01:51,695 --> 00:01:56,246
Really? You are the chair
of a chemistry department.

36
00:01:56,408 --> 00:01:59,537
You've spent a career sharing knowledge!

37
00:01:59,703 --> 00:02:01,000
No!

38
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:03,624
(SIGHING)

39
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:05,960
(EXHALES)

40
00:02:07,044 --> 00:02:08,967
(INHALING) I apologize.

41
00:02:12,049 --> 00:02:14,768
(EXHALING) I'm not myself these days.

42
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:20,482
Hands, please.

43
00:02:25,062 --> 00:02:28,908
I can be a member of a group,
but I can never blend in. What am I?

44
00:02:29,066 --> 00:02:31,785
I... A shadow?

45
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:37,453
The answer is an individual.

46
00:02:37,616 --> 00:02:39,835
Duh! I expected more.

47
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:44,256
But then, none of the others
did very well either.

48
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:46,087
- The others?
- Oh, you'd know them.

49
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:51,426
One was an artist, one was a writer,

50
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:55,008
one was a philosopher.

51
00:02:57,094 --> 00:02:59,973
The stars of Gotham's

52
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:04,109
intellectual and artistic constellation.

53
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:07,070
Fallen stars, now.

54
00:03:07,229 --> 00:03:08,731
Why are you doing this?

55
00:03:09,356 --> 00:03:10,357
(EXHALES)

56
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:13,990
My best friend recently said

57
00:03:14,152 --> 00:03:17,907
there was no me without him.

58
00:03:20,992 --> 00:03:22,619
I shot him and dumped him in the river.

59
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:27,383
He was a sort of guide to me
on my journey.

60
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:31,296
You see, I know who I am, Professor.

61
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:37,309
It's how to be him that is eluding me.

62
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:39,727
I seek guidance.

63
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:43,435
I feel your every move,
I know your every thought,

64
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:47,023
I'm with you from birth,
and I'll see you when you rot.

65
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,186
What am I?

66
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:50,822
I don't know!

67
00:03:52,649 --> 00:03:54,151
Well, that's just too bad.

68
00:03:58,488 --> 00:04:00,081
- (GAS HISSING)
- (ED WHISTLING)

69
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:06,163
No. No!

70
00:04:11,835 --> 00:04:14,133
- (GLASS SHATTERING)
- (CAR ALARMS BLARING)

71
00:04:14,713 --> 00:04:16,761
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

72
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:22,459
BRUCE: We'd gone to the movies.

73
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:26,854
My father wanted to cut through the alley
to get an uptown cab.

74
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:30,316
The man came out of nowhere.

75
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,857
His face was covered.

76
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:35,825
He had a gun.

77
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:39,492
I remember how cold it was.

78
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:43,751
I heard a cat.
He shot them both, and I did...

79
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,914
I did nothing.

80
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:51,379
Excellent, my dear.

81
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:54,628
You truly are Bruce Wayne.

82
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:01,718
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

83
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:07,144
- Yes.
- KATHRYN: We're ready.

84
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,901
Then proceed. I'll see you tomorrow.

85
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:13,781
And on your end?
I hope your nephew is amenable.

86
00:05:14,064 --> 00:05:17,284
Should he refuse,
you know what must happen.

87
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:19,444
I know the rules, Kathryn.

88
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,405
KATHRYN: We are to proceed.

89
00:05:27,744 --> 00:05:28,916
Do the rest.

90
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:35,923
Alfred Pennyworth is my guardian.

91
00:05:36,253 --> 00:05:39,257
He has been with me since I can remember.

92
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:58,283
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)

93
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:00,993
(INHALING AND EXHALING)

94
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:05,536
What did I tell you
about dripping on the couch?

95
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:07,076
You are the only person I know

96
00:06:07,242 --> 00:06:10,792
who frets about his drug-induced
hallucination making a mess. But...

97
00:06:12,873 --> 00:06:14,967
- If it makes you happy.
- Thank you.

98
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:18,132
I wonder how long you will be
the public face of grief

99
00:06:18,295 --> 00:06:20,889
when people hear
that you killed your best friend.

100
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:30,023
And then there are
your extracurricular activities.

101
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:34,319
How many are we up to now?

102
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,479
Five? Six?

103
00:06:38,273 --> 00:06:42,153
There was the curator.
The writer, pretentious ass.

104
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:44,450
It's so frustrating.

105
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:49,247
They all fit the profile, high I.Q.,
driven, creative.

106
00:06:50,285 --> 00:06:52,287
Yet, each one failed.

107
00:06:53,914 --> 00:06:55,474
You must be the first person in history

108
00:06:55,624 --> 00:06:57,877
to go on a killing spree
in order to find a life coach.

109
00:06:58,043 --> 00:07:00,341
Perhaps you should ditch the riddles.

110
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:04,349
No. A good riddle reveals the asker.

111
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,885
To solve it is to solve the mystery
of the person posing it.

112
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:10,147
If I can find someone to solve my riddles,

113
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:11,505
I can find someone to help me.

114
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:12,978
Do you really think
you're going to find someone

115
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:14,438
who can teach you how to be a villain?

116
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:16,729
Yes! Of course I am.

117
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:20,858
You said yourself, there is no
Edward Nygma without the Penguin.

118
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:24,118
But knowing who I am

119
00:07:25,195 --> 00:07:27,539
and knowing how to be him,
those are separate things.

120
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,825
Ed, villains do not have teachers!

121
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:33,708
I made myself into the Penguin
when I threw Fish Mooney off a building.

122
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:36,965
I didn't have anyone's help.

123
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:38,875
Oh, how interesting.

124
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:41,765
Perhaps I'm thinking about this all wrong.

125
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:43,138
Obviously.

126
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:46,971
I don't need a teacher. I need an enemy.

127
00:07:47,342 --> 00:07:48,343
No, that is not...

128
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:50,394
The greatest villains
have always been defined

129
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:53,397
by the men that try to stop them!

130
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:56,060
And I know the perfect man.

131
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,735
Please, do not say...

132
00:08:00,897 --> 00:08:02,399
Jim Gordon.

133
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:07,453
A serial killer of smart people?

134
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:09,406
In the last few weeks, six members

135
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:11,958
of Gotham's intellectual
and artistic elite

136
00:08:12,117 --> 00:08:14,791
have killed themselves
or died in strange accidents.

137
00:08:14,953 --> 00:08:18,048
Last night, an old professor of mine
died in a lab fire.

138
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:20,169
At a certain point,
coincidence becomes pattern.

139
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:23,431
You getting bored down in the lab, Lucius?

140
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:25,676
Yes, but that is not
why you should look at this.

141
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:30,936
Listen, we are still finding bodies
from Jerome's night of murder of mayhem.

142
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:34,849
Not to mention,
out looking for our dear missing mayor.

143
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:39,020
I do not have the resources
to allocate to your hunch.

144
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:42,189
Did you hear how I used
that word "allocate", hmm?

145
00:08:43,273 --> 00:08:45,116
- Let me call Gordon.
- No. No.

146
00:08:45,275 --> 00:08:47,619
The man's due R and R. Besides,

147
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:51,247
he's reconnecting with some
long-lost uncle or something.

148
00:08:51,448 --> 00:08:54,122
Jim Gordon? Detective Jim Gordon?

149
00:08:54,284 --> 00:08:55,456
Gordon ain't here.

150
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:57,461
So give me the message, fruit guy.

151
00:08:59,164 --> 00:09:00,290
(KAZOO BUZZING)

152
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,168
(SINGING) Six masters have passed

153
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:05,132
There's about to be more

154
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:08,799
A king, a queen and their corps

155
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:11,138
The key to saving them

156
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:12,928
Is on this card

157
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:15,893
So won 't you please help them
By making...

158
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,565
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

159
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:19,664
- One more time!
- (OFFICER LAUGHING)

160
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:21,978
What the hell is this?

161
00:09:23,146 --> 00:09:26,776
"Six masters passed."
That could be the six murders.

162
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:27,984
I told you...

163
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:30,787
Harvey, the killer's sending
Gordon a clue.

164
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:32,409
He's gonna kill again.

165
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:35,075
Okay, say you're right.
Now, which way is up on this thing?

166
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,288
Let me see that.

167
00:09:36,493 --> 00:09:39,963
"A king, a queen and her corp."
It's a drawing of the Knight's Tour.

168
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:43,671
Right. So the target is...

169
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:47,841
Come on.

170
00:09:49,172 --> 00:09:50,344
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

171
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:52,054
(TIMERS CLICKING)

172
00:09:56,221 --> 00:09:58,019
- (HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)
- (EXHALING)

173
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:02,977
(INHALES)

174
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:09,484
- Thanks for coming.
- Like I had a choice?

175
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:11,452
Oh, you'll thank me.

176
00:10:13,196 --> 00:10:14,664
This is gonna be electrifying.

177
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,282
(INHALING)

178
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,423
(LED BUZZING)

179
00:10:29,671 --> 00:10:31,071
Knight to Queen three. Mate in two.

180
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:33,738
MAN: Quiet, please.
ED: Oh, honestly.

181
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:36,887
They call anyone a Grandmaster these days.

182
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:39,889
Can we discuss why you're doing this?

183
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:42,017
I've told you why.

184
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,943
The real reason.

185
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:45,103
(PACKET RUSTLING)

186
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:51,656
See, Ed, the trouble with
talking to projections of your psyche,

187
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:53,411
and you of all people should know this,

188
00:10:53,945 --> 00:10:57,119
is that they know everything you know.

189
00:10:57,574 --> 00:11:00,327
Including the things
you're trying not to know.

190
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:02,412
Gordon can't help you.

191
00:11:03,037 --> 00:11:04,289
No one can.

192
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:05,581
Face the truth.

193
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,134
(DOOR OPENING)

194
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:21,606
Excuse me, sir.
Only players are allowed on the floor.

195
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:23,687
No Jim Gordon.

196
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,484
But then, who solved...

197
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:26,644
(GASPING)

198
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:29,231
Of course. How can I help you?

199
00:11:29,397 --> 00:11:31,650
Yes, ma'am, we need to
evacuate the building immediately.

200
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:35,282
We're in the middle of an important
tournament. Are you sure?

201
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:38,456
Maybe I was wrong.
Maybe this isn't the place.

202
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:41,535
Oh, how interesting.

203
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:44,124
Checkmate!

204
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:46,497
- (PEOPLE SCREAMING)
- (ED LAUGHS)

205
00:11:46,789 --> 00:11:48,587
GCPD! Everybody out!

206
00:11:50,627 --> 00:11:51,753
Don't move, freeze!

207
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:53,467
Forget what I just said.

208
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,428
Freeze. Do not move...

209
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:56,591
(LAUGHING)

210
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:00,474
JIM: Why am I here, Uncle Frank?

211
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:03,357
Maybe you wanna tell me where the
hell you've been since I was a kid.

212
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:05,604
Or what happened between you and my dad.

213
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:07,485
Yes. Yes, I do.

214
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:10,939
But I need to know that you trust me.

215
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:15,118
You're family. Of course I trust you.

216
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:19,156
Did you ever do something
you thought was right at the time,

217
00:12:19,322 --> 00:12:22,041
but would now give your life to do over?

218
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:24,202
Yes.

219
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:27,464
Looking back, I've done
too many terrible things like that.

220
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:30,838
But the worst was break from your father.

221
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:32,961
Keep talking.

222
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:34,629
I loved my brother Peter dearly,

223
00:12:35,505 --> 00:12:37,223
and you're my brother's son.

224
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,684
I came back to Gotham because of you, Jim.

225
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:43,476
I want to make things right between us.

226
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:49,524
So, you shift your weight to your front
foot as you swing your arm forward,

227
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:51,089
just like chopping down a branch.

228
00:12:51,229 --> 00:12:53,357
Like... Easy as pie.

229
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,446
Right, so, weight on the back foot.

230
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:59,658
- Blade comes back evenly, and, well...
- (SHUSHING)

231
00:12:59,904 --> 00:13:03,283
Precision under pressure is everything,
Master Bruce.

232
00:13:04,784 --> 00:13:06,502
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

233
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:08,459
- And a clear conscience.
- (GRUNTS)

234
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:11,503
Were you aiming for the window,
Master Bruce?

235
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:12,800
You keep distracting me.

236
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:15,257
Well, you should be able to hit
the target regardless, shouldn't you?

237
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,714
I mean, we had rules about training.

238
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:21,930
Rules which will be impossible to stand by
if you remain unfocused.

239
00:13:22,093 --> 00:13:25,814
Now, I sense there's something
weighing on your mind.

240
00:13:27,015 --> 00:13:28,562
Miss Kyle, perhaps?

241
00:13:28,725 --> 00:13:30,227
I'm not unfocused because of Selina.

242
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:31,736
Oh! Right, I see. Right.

243
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:33,294
So, it wouldn't trouble you to know

244
00:13:33,396 --> 00:13:36,115
that she dropped a note
off for you in the mailbox, then.

245
00:13:36,566 --> 00:13:38,910
She asked to see you tomorrow.

246
00:13:41,738 --> 00:13:42,739
No.

247
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:47,247
Selina's been avoiding me for weeks.

248
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:52,048
It's gonna take more than a note
to have me running.

249
00:13:54,459 --> 00:13:55,961
(POLICE SIRENS BLARING)

250
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:06,854
I got Alvarez and Campos
looking into the other egghead deaths.

251
00:14:07,013 --> 00:14:08,139
Hopefully, something will kick up.

252
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:11,276
Or else we could sit around and wait
for him to send us more singing fruit.

253
00:14:11,642 --> 00:14:13,861
Maybe he has sent us a clue.

254
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:15,104
BULLOCK: Ohhh.

255
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:18,115
BULLOCK: Oh-ho-ho.
LUCIUS: Mmm-hmm.

256
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,944
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

257
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:23,450
- (PHONE BEEPS)
- You're late.

258
00:14:23,613 --> 00:14:25,707
I expected this call seven minutes ago.

259
00:14:26,157 --> 00:14:28,205
This is Lucius Fox of the GCPD.

260
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:30,457
I know who you are, Mr. Fox.

261
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:33,804
And by the way, it's bad manners
to intercept other people's mail.

262
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:35,833
You mean the telegram you sent Gordon.

263
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,718
He's not here. Who is this?

264
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:39,917
You don't actually expect me
to answer that, do you?

265
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:42,014
Then tell me why you killed
Professor Dyson and the others.

266
00:14:42,215 --> 00:14:44,309
- I know it was you.
- I had no choice.

267
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:45,684
They failed my test.

268
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:47,390
Now it's your turn to try.

269
00:14:48,137 --> 00:14:50,435
And if I don't accept the invitation?

270
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:53,484
There are lives at stake, Mr. Fox.

271
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:55,812
And not just your own.
Now, listen closely.

272
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:58,147
Tomorrow, when the pawn's on queen,

273
00:14:58,314 --> 00:15:00,487
you'll find my next target
in the belly of the beast.

274
00:15:00,650 --> 00:15:03,950
Solve my clue, Mr. Fox,

275
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:07,958
and you'll be one step closer
to passing my test.

276
00:15:08,116 --> 00:15:09,117
(TELEPHONE BEEPS)

277
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:12,252
"When the pawn's on queen"?

278
00:15:12,537 --> 00:15:13,880
"Belly of the beast."

279
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:18,426
And I'll be one step closer
to introducing myself to Gotham

280
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:21,675
once and for all.

281
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,185
(GUNSHOT)

282
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:40,523
Close. Better luck next time.

283
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:42,320
I missed on purpose.

284
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,026
Oh?

285
00:15:44,861 --> 00:15:46,238
Wanted to make sure my gun works.

286
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:49,536
Oh, come on, Jim. What do you take me for?

287
00:15:49,699 --> 00:15:51,201
I have no idea.

288
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:53,687
You say you've done terrible things,
you bring me out here,

289
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:55,712
you promise me the truth,
and I'm still waiting.

290
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:59,584
If this is a trust-building exercise,
it's not working.

291
00:16:00,418 --> 00:16:03,171
What happened between you and my father?

292
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:08,934
Have you ever heard the old Gotham tales
about the Court of Owls?

293
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:14,515
Pretend I haven't.

294
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:21,189
The Court is a secret society
that's controlled Gotham for centuries.

295
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:24,985
Started by its oldest, wealthiest,
most influential families.

296
00:16:25,151 --> 00:16:29,247
The Court was once a mechanism
devoted to maintaining balance in Gotham.

297
00:16:29,864 --> 00:16:32,333
But time and power have corrupted them.

298
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:35,077
If it's so secret,
how do you know about them?

299
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:37,247
Your father and I were both members.

300
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:40,333
I still am a member.

301
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,427
Is that so?

302
00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:49,345
The Court doesn't mean you any harm.

303
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:51,932
They have the highest regard for you.

304
00:16:52,178 --> 00:16:53,930
In fact, they want you to become a member.

305
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:58,851
(TRAIN RATTLING)

306
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,941
Peters, we got a tip from a guy

307
00:17:01,103 --> 00:17:04,277
who electrocuted a bunch of players
at a fancy chess tournament

308
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:06,408
pointing us to a pawn on queens.

309
00:17:06,609 --> 00:17:09,453
Now, here, you work at a pawnshop
on Queens Avenue.

310
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:10,864
Coincidence? No.

311
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,533
So? I don't know nothing about that.

312
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:15,292
Why you so close to me?

313
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:17,124
Many interrogators employ the tactic

314
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:20,130
of invading someone's personal space
to destabilize them.

315
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:23,342
Do you feel destabilized, Mr. Peters?

316
00:17:23,501 --> 00:17:24,861
(LAUGHING) Is this guy even a cop?

317
00:17:24,961 --> 00:17:26,963
Hey! We can do this the hard way
or the easy way.

318
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:29,928
And I'm wearing my nicest suit,
so I'd prefer the easy way.

319
00:17:30,091 --> 00:17:32,765
- Hey, screw you.
- All right, Lucius, hit him.

320
00:17:33,094 --> 00:17:34,141
- What?
- What?

321
00:17:34,303 --> 00:17:35,520
I'm wearing my nice suit.

322
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:37,811
We're disregarding
the latter half of the clue.

323
00:17:37,974 --> 00:17:39,772
It said we'd find the target
in the belly of the beast.

324
00:17:39,934 --> 00:17:43,984
Oh, if you wanna do a cavity search
on this slob, go ahead, be my guest.

325
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:45,944
- Hey, you could just hit me.
- No one's hitting anyone.

326
00:17:46,107 --> 00:17:47,587
I wasn't even supposed to work today.

327
00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:50,620
I was covering for Teddy Thirio,
the owner's cousin.

328
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:54,074
Thirio. That's the Greek word for "beast."

329
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:57,335
You know, sometimes, I think
you just make that stuff up. Come on.

330
00:18:03,332 --> 00:18:05,130
What are you making?

331
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:07,920
- Shepherd's pie.
- Again?

332
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:10,727
Well, you're more than welcome
to take over the menu, Master Bruce.

333
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:14,265
Did I ever tell you how I copped this
recipe from an old lady friend of mine?

334
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,730
Sylvia. A memorable fling.

335
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:22,519
Ended badly, though. Can't remember
what we rowed about. Something idiotic.

336
00:18:22,685 --> 00:18:24,813
It left me reeling, Master Bruce.

337
00:18:24,979 --> 00:18:26,856
I couldn't concentrate on my studies.

338
00:18:27,023 --> 00:18:30,243
Really? You think telling me a transparent
anecdote will make me run to Selina?

339
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:33,120
No, I don't.
You see, Sylvia and I, we got closure.

340
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:36,129
Now, it seems that Miss Kyle
has offered you the same opportunity,

341
00:18:36,157 --> 00:18:39,036
and I suggest that you... You take it.

342
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:46,758
Fine.

343
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:50,338
If it'll get you to stop, I'll go.

344
00:18:50,504 --> 00:18:53,348
I'll keep the pie warm for you,
Master Bruce.

345
00:18:53,716 --> 00:18:54,836
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

346
00:18:54,884 --> 00:18:56,181
Thirio's not in his apartment.

347
00:18:56,677 --> 00:18:59,396
Have Campos put out a city-wide BOLO.

348
00:18:59,555 --> 00:19:01,228
I'm going to the Academy graduation.

349
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:04,860
I have to, uh, impart my wisdom
on the new cadets.

350
00:19:05,019 --> 00:19:06,692
How do I look?

351
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:08,527
Is this what Gordon deals with?

352
00:19:09,023 --> 00:19:12,118
Thank you. Have you seen my badge?

353
00:19:13,903 --> 00:19:15,576
"The Chess Killer."

354
00:19:15,905 --> 00:19:17,077
How terrifying.

355
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:20,250
How will anyone sleep knowing
the Chess Killer is on the loose?

356
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:23,288
It's just a name dreamed up by some hack.
Today will change everything.

357
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:25,752
- This is a mistake, what you're doing.
- I don't recall asking you.

358
00:19:25,915 --> 00:19:27,838
I showed you how to be Ed Nygma,

359
00:19:28,042 --> 00:19:31,421
a man who could run the underworld
and operate in plain sight.

360
00:19:31,629 --> 00:19:33,631
What you are planning is madness.

361
00:19:33,798 --> 00:19:36,176
No. It's a way forward.

362
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:38,185
And the fact that it scares you

363
00:19:38,344 --> 00:19:40,312
gives me all the confirmation I need.

364
00:19:40,471 --> 00:19:43,065
Ed, you are not sleeping.
You are taking drugs.

365
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:45,568
You are having a conversation
with your dead friend.

366
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:49,606
Just admit that you are lost without me,
or you will destroy everything!

367
00:19:49,772 --> 00:19:50,898
I have to go.

368
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:55,615
- (VINYL SCRATCHING)
- (MUSIC PLAYING)

369
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,078
What are you doing?

370
00:19:57,947 --> 00:20:01,417
(SINGING)
He's fierce in my dreams, seizing my guts

371
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:05,205
He floats me with dread

372
00:20:05,413 --> 00:20:06,881
Soaked in his soul

373
00:20:07,081 --> 00:20:11,757
He swims in my eyes by the bed

374
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:14,888
Pour myself over him

375
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:17,675
Moon spilling in

376
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:22,813
And I wake up alone

377
00:20:23,848 --> 00:20:28,103
Enough! I admit that killing you
killed a part of me.

378
00:20:29,186 --> 00:20:32,486
But I will find a way forward,
no matter the cost.

379
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:35,155
I will be born anew!

380
00:20:35,317 --> 00:20:37,194
And I will leave you behind.

381
00:20:37,445 --> 00:20:41,325
Penguin saw you, Ed. He was the only one!
He made you!

382
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:45,120
There is no Ed Nygma without the Penguin!

383
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:48,956
DR. THOMPKINS: Meet Ted Thirio.
Came in about an hour ago.

384
00:20:49,123 --> 00:20:51,404
Cause of death seems to be
blunt force trauma to the head.

385
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,003
However, Mr. Thirio also has
a long incision

386
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:57,344
along the right side of his abdomen
that's been crudely stapled shut.

387
00:20:57,506 --> 00:21:00,680
The Chess Killer promised a clue
inside the belly of the beast.

388
00:21:00,926 --> 00:21:02,849
Think there might be something
in his stomach.

389
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:07,350
- Okay.
- You worked at Arkham Asylum.

390
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:11,362
Why would a killer
engage in this kind of cat and mouse?

391
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:15,650
Crazy or sane, at the core, most people
just want answers to life's big questions.

392
00:21:15,858 --> 00:21:17,075
"Will I ever be loved?"

393
00:21:17,485 --> 00:21:18,611
"Who am I?"

394
00:21:18,819 --> 00:21:20,366
Although, most people
try to answer the question

395
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:23,533
in a logical fashion, while others...

396
00:21:26,494 --> 00:21:27,495
Hmm.

397
00:21:28,621 --> 00:21:30,919
Stuff Harvey Bullock's badge
inside a dead body.

398
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:32,207
What does that mean?

399
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:34,756
It means I know who the next target is.
Thank you, Doctor.

400
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:35,920
Uh...

401
00:21:36,086 --> 00:21:38,430
Thank you, Doctor. Sorry. I know.
Thank you.

402
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,301
(CLEARS THROAT)

403
00:21:42,468 --> 00:21:44,766
"As you take the badge today,

404
00:21:44,929 --> 00:21:49,400
"approach Gotham as you would
a cut of prime rib.

405
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:53,153
"Have a plan, don't be afraid,

406
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:57,067
"and have plenty of antacids on hand
in case of indigestion."

407
00:21:57,233 --> 00:21:59,110
(SLOW CLAPPING)

408
00:22:00,945 --> 00:22:02,413
What the hell are you doing here?

409
00:22:02,571 --> 00:22:07,247
Well, seeing as how your department
is unable to locate our missing mayor,

410
00:22:07,535 --> 00:22:10,209
I'm here to give the graduating class
a few remarks in his stead.

411
00:22:10,371 --> 00:22:14,342
There's no way I'm letting a cop killer
address those cadets.

412
00:22:14,542 --> 00:22:18,092
I see. How is the view from the moral
high ground, Harvey?

413
00:22:18,254 --> 00:22:20,427
View's perfect. Now, get lost.

414
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,592
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

415
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:26,307
Oh, Lucius Fox. Must be about me.

416
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:37,898
(CAR HORNS BEEPING)

417
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:41,865
SONNY: Wanna play? You guys wanna play?
You wanna play? Come on.

418
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:43,070
(MAN GRUNTING)

419
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:46,198
(SONNY LAUGHING)

420
00:22:48,951 --> 00:22:52,706
- I'm looking for Selina Kyle.
- Oh. I remember you. Bruce Wayne.

421
00:22:52,872 --> 00:22:54,872
- Listen, I don't want any trouble.
- SON NY: Sure.

422
00:22:55,875 --> 00:22:57,297
- How much cash you got?
- MAN: Get him, Sonny.

423
00:22:57,459 --> 00:22:59,632
SELINA: Stop!
MAN: Yeah, do it. Go on, do it.

424
00:22:59,837 --> 00:23:01,714
Sonny, I said back off!

425
00:23:06,135 --> 00:23:09,105
- What are you doing here?
- BRUCE: Looking for you.

426
00:23:09,471 --> 00:23:11,144
- Can we go somewhere?
- SELINA: No.

427
00:23:12,141 --> 00:23:14,064
I gotta talk to Sonny.

428
00:23:14,435 --> 00:23:15,482
We got business.

429
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:20,320
Oh.
Does that shock your tender sensibilities?

430
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:22,026
- He's a thief.
- I’m a thief.

431
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:23,861
- BRUCE: You can't trust him.
- But I can trust you?

432
00:23:24,194 --> 00:23:25,696
Look, I'm sorry.

433
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:27,698
I should've told you I suspected
your mother of lying.

434
00:23:27,865 --> 00:23:29,082
I was trying to protect you, Selina.

435
00:23:29,283 --> 00:23:30,830
I can protect myself.

436
00:23:32,328 --> 00:23:33,830
Just go home, Bruce.

437
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:36,624
(SCOFFS) You don't belong here.

438
00:23:40,336 --> 00:23:43,465
Why'd you ask me here
if you were going to be this way?

439
00:23:44,173 --> 00:23:45,253
What are you talking about?

440
00:23:46,050 --> 00:23:48,018
The note you left in my mailbox.

441
00:23:49,053 --> 00:23:50,305
I didn't leave any note.

442
00:23:52,181 --> 00:23:55,310
Don't come looking for me again.

443
00:23:56,310 --> 00:23:58,187
We'll talk later, Sonny.

444
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:03,825
SONNY: (SIGHS)
Too bad your girlfriend split.

445
00:24:06,362 --> 00:24:08,785
- I don't think she's my girlfriend.
- (CHUCKLING)

446
00:24:11,408 --> 00:24:12,785
Me neither.

447
00:24:14,078 --> 00:24:15,580
So, about that money.

448
00:24:16,497 --> 00:24:17,498
(GRUNTING)

449
00:24:17,831 --> 00:24:18,832
(YELLING)

450
00:24:20,292 --> 00:24:21,572
MAN 1: It's my turn.
MAN 2: Whoo!

451
00:24:21,627 --> 00:24:22,628
(MEN JEERING)

452
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:26,048
SONNY: Poor Brucey.

453
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:29,514
Staying down there, huh, big boy?

454
00:24:30,052 --> 00:24:32,225
Oh, oh, he's up. Big boy.

455
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:34,264
(GRUNTING)

456
00:24:36,642 --> 00:24:37,643
(YELLING)

457
00:24:44,066 --> 00:24:45,739
(TRAIN RATTLING)

458
00:24:46,777 --> 00:24:48,871
- (CROWD CHATTERING)
- (MICROPHONE FEEDBACK)

459
00:24:50,948 --> 00:24:52,245
Hello, cadets.

460
00:24:53,742 --> 00:24:56,211
My name is Edward Nygma.

461
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:58,839
Captain Bullock's tied up.

462
00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:02,922
What a day, eh?

463
00:25:04,086 --> 00:25:07,431
You all look just dandy in your uniforms.

464
00:25:08,007 --> 00:25:09,008
How do I look?

465
00:25:09,174 --> 00:25:10,175
(CONFUSED CHATTERING)

466
00:25:10,592 --> 00:25:11,593
(CHUCKLING)

467
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,770
I have one question for all of you.

468
00:25:14,430 --> 00:25:17,274
Light as a feather,
yet no man can hold it long.

469
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:19,351
(MICROPHONE FEEDBACK)

470
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:20,561
What am I?

471
00:25:21,895 --> 00:25:22,896
(CROWD CHATTERING)

472
00:25:26,567 --> 00:25:28,945
Well, no future commissioners here.

473
00:25:29,987 --> 00:25:31,204
The answer is...

474
00:25:31,697 --> 00:25:32,698
(METAL CLINKING)

475
00:25:34,158 --> 00:25:35,159
(OBJECT RATTLING)

476
00:25:38,996 --> 00:25:39,997
(GAS HISSING)

477
00:25:40,831 --> 00:25:42,083
Your breath.

478
00:25:48,964 --> 00:25:49,965
(LAUGHING)

479
00:25:57,347 --> 00:25:59,224
- I think that's for me.
- You Foxy?

480
00:25:59,808 --> 00:26:00,855
Nygma.

481
00:26:01,310 --> 00:26:02,653
(PHONE RINGS)

482
00:26:03,645 --> 00:26:04,646
(PHONE BEEPS)

483
00:26:05,314 --> 00:26:06,315
Hello.

484
00:26:06,482 --> 00:26:08,450
Only one person refers to me as "Foxy."

485
00:26:08,609 --> 00:26:11,613
I have gassed a room full of folks
with a deadly toxin.

486
00:26:11,779 --> 00:26:16,080
I cordially invite you to come upstairs
and play a game with me for the antidote.

487
00:26:16,658 --> 00:26:18,626
This is a game between me and you.

488
00:26:18,869 --> 00:26:23,716
Come upstairs alone,
or the cadets and Bullock die.

489
00:26:23,874 --> 00:26:25,467
I'm on my way.

490
00:26:25,709 --> 00:26:26,710
(PHONE BEEPS)

491
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:31,723
(BULLOCK GRUNTING)

492
00:26:32,049 --> 00:26:36,225
Well, look who it is.
I'm so glad you decided to play.

493
00:26:36,804 --> 00:26:37,851
Are you okay, Harvey?

494
00:26:38,889 --> 00:26:40,891
Look at him! He's fine.

495
00:26:41,183 --> 00:26:42,685
I want to hear Harvey say he's okay.

496
00:26:46,188 --> 00:26:48,441
Don't try and outsmart this lunatic,
Lucius!

497
00:26:48,607 --> 00:26:50,484
Cadets' lives are at stake.

498
00:26:51,860 --> 00:26:52,861
Let's begin.

499
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:57,370
Wonderful. I will give you three riddles.

500
00:26:57,574 --> 00:27:00,874
For every riddle you get wrong,
I cut a rope.

501
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:04,757
You get three wrong, and this excuse
for a higher primate,

502
00:27:04,915 --> 00:27:07,589
and the antidote around his neck...

503
00:27:08,961 --> 00:27:09,962
(WHISTLES)

504
00:27:10,379 --> 00:27:12,598
Fall over the ledge.

505
00:27:12,881 --> 00:27:13,882
(GROANING)

506
00:27:14,508 --> 00:27:15,885
ED: Wow.
(WHISTLES)

507
00:27:17,761 --> 00:27:19,058
Am I clear?

508
00:27:19,221 --> 00:27:20,518
And if I get them right?

509
00:27:21,098 --> 00:27:22,395
Everyone lives.

510
00:27:22,558 --> 00:27:25,027
Even if you get just one.

511
00:27:25,686 --> 00:27:27,563
Can't say fairer than that?

512
00:27:27,771 --> 00:27:28,772
(ROPES CREAKING)

513
00:27:29,815 --> 00:27:30,816
Okay.

514
00:27:30,983 --> 00:27:31,984
(KNIFE CLICKS)

515
00:27:32,401 --> 00:27:33,744
Wonderful.

516
00:27:34,778 --> 00:27:38,783
First riddle,
I can fill a room or just one heart.

517
00:27:38,949 --> 00:27:41,452
Others can have me, but I can't be shared.

518
00:27:41,910 --> 00:27:43,457
What am I?

519
00:27:44,288 --> 00:27:45,289
The answer's love.

520
00:27:47,291 --> 00:27:49,544
What? No.

521
00:27:51,086 --> 00:27:52,963
No! The...

522
00:27:54,131 --> 00:27:56,054
The answer is loneliness!

523
00:27:56,216 --> 00:27:58,059
How do you not know that?

524
00:27:58,260 --> 00:28:01,104
No, no. No. No, Nygma, no!

525
00:28:01,430 --> 00:28:02,431
Oh, God!

526
00:28:03,056 --> 00:28:04,057
(YELLING)

527
00:28:09,605 --> 00:28:10,982
Ask me another.

528
00:28:11,148 --> 00:28:13,196
Okay. Second riddle,

529
00:28:13,525 --> 00:28:16,495
I can be a member of a group,
but can never blend in.

530
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:17,696
What am I?

531
00:28:21,158 --> 00:28:22,284
A snowflake.

532
00:28:22,618 --> 00:28:23,790
A sn...

533
00:28:24,912 --> 00:28:27,631
No! No! No!

534
00:28:27,956 --> 00:28:30,129
The answer is an individual.

535
00:28:30,918 --> 00:28:34,639
Wait. Snowflake is also a suitable answer.

536
00:28:34,796 --> 00:28:38,300
No two are alike,
making them by definition, individuals.

537
00:28:38,467 --> 00:28:41,095
Therefore,
an answer befitting your riddle.

538
00:28:41,303 --> 00:28:45,149
Okay, I don't think you grasp
how this works.

539
00:28:45,349 --> 00:28:47,351
You have to give my answer.

540
00:28:47,935 --> 00:28:50,108
(GROANING)

541
00:28:51,855 --> 00:28:52,856
(YELLING)

542
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:55,821
Oh, mama, I'm sorry! Oh, God!

543
00:28:58,028 --> 00:28:59,621
Oswald was right.

544
00:28:59,780 --> 00:29:01,908
He's the only one...

545
00:29:03,283 --> 00:29:06,287
No! It's just you.

546
00:29:07,829 --> 00:29:10,332
You aren't a good enough enemy!

547
00:29:12,459 --> 00:29:13,881
No. No.

548
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:21,227
No. Three riddles, three answers.
Those are the rules, Ed.

549
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:25,393
Okay. Final riddle,
I feel your every move,

550
00:29:25,555 --> 00:29:28,104
I know your every thought,
I'm with you from birth,

551
00:29:28,267 --> 00:29:31,020
and I'll see you rot. What am I?

552
00:29:31,186 --> 00:29:32,779
What did you do, Ed?

553
00:29:33,981 --> 00:29:36,825
What did you... What happened to Penguin?

554
00:29:40,153 --> 00:29:42,702
Something happened, didn't it?

555
00:29:44,032 --> 00:29:45,500
(ED GRUNTS)

556
00:29:46,118 --> 00:29:47,119
Did you kill him?

557
00:29:48,245 --> 00:29:51,340
This is not gonna be good.
Please don't let me go this...

558
00:29:51,540 --> 00:29:52,660
LUCIUS: You did, didn't you?

559
00:29:52,708 --> 00:29:55,757
I feel your every thought,
I feel your every move,

560
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:58,388
I know your every thought,
I'm with you from birth,

561
00:29:58,547 --> 00:30:00,049
and I'll see you rot.

562
00:30:01,091 --> 00:30:02,434
What am I?

563
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:05,349
A reflection.

564
00:30:06,388 --> 00:30:08,561
Why does it always
have to be three answers?

565
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:11,352
Why can't he get four? Come on!

566
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:12,937
Correct.

567
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:16,350
- (ROPE SNAPPING)
- (YELLING)

568
00:30:16,732 --> 00:30:17,733
Oops.

569
00:30:17,899 --> 00:30:19,116
- (ROPE SNAPS)
- (YELLING)

570
00:30:21,862 --> 00:30:22,863
(STRAINING)

571
00:30:25,741 --> 00:30:27,163
(SIGHS HAPPILY)

572
00:30:27,784 --> 00:30:29,331
(PANTING) Thanks, buddy.

573
00:30:29,786 --> 00:30:31,254
I never doubted you.

574
00:30:34,416 --> 00:30:36,714
(POLICE SIRENS BLARING IN DISTANCE)

575
00:30:49,014 --> 00:30:50,015
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

576
00:30:57,481 --> 00:30:58,573
You.

577
00:30:59,441 --> 00:31:00,784
What are you doing here?

578
00:31:02,944 --> 00:31:04,321
It's good to see you, too.

579
00:31:05,447 --> 00:31:06,664
How'd things go with Selina?

580
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:09,705
How did you...

581
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:12,792
You sent that note.

582
00:31:17,834 --> 00:31:20,838
And you're dressed like me.
Even your hair.

583
00:31:21,004 --> 00:31:23,883
Yes. Like looking into a mirror.

584
00:31:27,052 --> 00:31:28,850
A powerful knock-out drug.

585
00:31:30,138 --> 00:31:31,139
(BRUCE GRUNTS)

586
00:31:36,061 --> 00:31:37,062
Why?

587
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:40,274
This is what I was made for.

588
00:31:46,947 --> 00:31:50,292
To be Bruce Wayne.

589
00:31:58,333 --> 00:32:02,054
How could you, how could my father
have been a part of this?

590
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,298
We were proud to join.

591
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:08,013
We thought we were gonna do good.

592
00:32:09,052 --> 00:32:10,679
The Court lied to us.

593
00:32:10,971 --> 00:32:12,973
Or we lied to ourselves, I don't know.

594
00:32:13,140 --> 00:32:15,859
And now? You're still a loyal member?

595
00:32:16,101 --> 00:32:17,444
They think so.

596
00:32:17,894 --> 00:32:20,443
I was a true believer, God help me.

597
00:32:22,399 --> 00:32:24,367
I despise them with every bone in my body.

598
00:32:25,068 --> 00:32:26,991
What changed your mind?

599
00:32:27,154 --> 00:32:29,907
Your father saw through their lies.

600
00:32:30,365 --> 00:32:32,959
I didn't listen to him
until it was too late.

601
00:32:33,201 --> 00:32:34,748
When was too late?

602
00:32:36,163 --> 00:32:37,164
When they killed him.

603
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:38,373
No.

604
00:32:39,291 --> 00:32:43,262
No. I was there.
It was an accident, a drunk driver.

605
00:32:43,503 --> 00:32:44,755
Just looked that way.

606
00:32:45,464 --> 00:32:49,139
I was there. I was in the wreck!
I watched him die.

607
00:32:49,301 --> 00:32:51,724
Car wrecks like that
are simple business for the Court.

608
00:32:52,429 --> 00:32:55,273
My brother was making trouble,
and they killed him.

609
00:32:55,432 --> 00:32:56,979
Sure as I'm standing here now.

610
00:32:57,642 --> 00:32:58,734
Now?

611
00:33:00,353 --> 00:33:03,607
Some 20-odd years later, and you come
and you tell me this crazy story?

612
00:33:03,773 --> 00:33:05,070
Where the hell have you been?

613
00:33:05,358 --> 00:33:07,156
Where were you
when my mom and I needed you?

614
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:09,579
I'm truly sorry I wasn't there for you,
Jim.

615
00:33:10,030 --> 00:33:11,907
I had no choice.

616
00:33:12,073 --> 00:33:14,872
The Court sent me overseas.
I had to prove my loyalty.

617
00:33:15,577 --> 00:33:19,081
How could you prove your loyalty
to a group that murdered your own brother?

618
00:33:19,247 --> 00:33:23,047
I knew they'd kill me if I didn't obey.
I chose to live.

619
00:33:23,710 --> 00:33:26,088
Until now. Why now?

620
00:33:26,588 --> 00:33:28,761
Because now,
you've been asked to join the Court.

621
00:33:28,924 --> 00:33:30,597
Now I'm not alone.

622
00:33:31,968 --> 00:33:33,185
Now...

623
00:33:34,721 --> 00:33:36,598
You can help me destroy them from within.

624
00:33:37,390 --> 00:33:39,609
Others have tried and failed.

625
00:33:39,768 --> 00:33:43,022
But with you and I working together
inside the Court,

626
00:33:43,188 --> 00:33:45,737
we can bring the rule of democracy
and law back to Gotham.

627
00:33:45,899 --> 00:33:48,322
Why should I trust you?
Why should I believe you?

628
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:50,779
Because we're family?

629
00:33:53,114 --> 00:33:55,116
You have to believe in something.

630
00:33:57,702 --> 00:33:59,750
FEMALE NEWSCASTER: And while all
the cadets survived the attack,

631
00:33:59,955 --> 00:34:02,458
police say the culprit,
former mayoral chief of staff,

632
00:34:02,624 --> 00:34:04,297
Edward Nygma, remains at large.

633
00:34:04,459 --> 00:34:07,303
Be on the lookout for a green suit.
That's right, a green...

634
00:34:07,462 --> 00:34:08,509
Good evening, Alfred.

635
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:10,765
And to you, Master Bruce.

636
00:34:11,466 --> 00:34:14,640
Well, you seem remarkably chipper.
Things went well with Ms. Kyle, I take it?

637
00:34:15,136 --> 00:34:17,514
- (SIGHING) Selina's Selina.
- Well, say no more.

638
00:34:17,889 --> 00:34:20,108
You spoke, that's all that matters, innit?

639
00:34:21,935 --> 00:34:23,415
You up for some shepherd's pie, then?

640
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:25,359
Sounds delicious.

641
00:34:26,648 --> 00:34:29,652
Right, jolly good. Won't be a moment.

642
00:34:37,284 --> 00:34:39,412
- (DOOR SLAMS OPEN)
- B-team, spread out.

643
00:34:40,287 --> 00:34:41,504
Lock down egress.

644
00:34:41,830 --> 00:34:43,832
MAN: All clear.
WOMAN: Clear!

645
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:46,876
Upstairs.

646
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:49,295
MAN: Clear!

647
00:34:50,630 --> 00:34:51,973
Captain, all clear.

648
00:34:53,675 --> 00:34:54,676
(SIGHS)

649
00:34:55,093 --> 00:34:57,721
I know. He's not here.

650
00:35:10,692 --> 00:35:11,693
(HORN HONKING)

651
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:15,697
(POLICE SIRENS BLARING IN DISTANCE)

652
00:35:26,207 --> 00:35:27,550
Hello, Foxy.

653
00:35:29,544 --> 00:35:31,091
(LAUGHS)

654
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:37,560
So, the antidote around Bullock's neck,
that turned out to be grape juice.

655
00:35:38,053 --> 00:35:39,054
(ED CHUCKLING)

656
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:41,643
And the deadly toxin?

657
00:35:41,806 --> 00:35:44,810
Plain old knock-out gas. Why the charade?

658
00:35:46,019 --> 00:35:48,238
Well, the point
wasn't to kill a bunch of cops.

659
00:35:48,396 --> 00:35:51,445
The point was to have you play my game.
(CHUCKLING)

660
00:35:51,608 --> 00:35:53,110
But you killed Penguin.

661
00:35:53,276 --> 00:35:56,906
And you killed Professor Dyson
and the others. Why?

662
00:35:57,989 --> 00:36:00,913
Have you always been Foxy, Foxy?

663
00:36:02,452 --> 00:36:04,420
I'm not sure what you mean.

664
00:36:06,581 --> 00:36:07,958
All my life,

665
00:36:09,417 --> 00:36:12,762
I've felt like there was someone
inside of me.

666
00:36:13,505 --> 00:36:17,385
Someone stronger and... And smarter.

667
00:36:19,052 --> 00:36:20,599
Someone that people would fear.

668
00:36:20,887 --> 00:36:22,309
No one else saw that.

669
00:36:22,472 --> 00:36:23,564
Except Penguin.

670
00:36:26,935 --> 00:36:29,438
- Except Oswald.
- So why did you kill him?

671
00:36:29,604 --> 00:36:32,699
Because Oswald killed the woman I loved.

672
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:37,158
And with Oswald gone,
is that the role I'm meant to fill?

673
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:38,492
To be your reflection?

674
00:36:38,655 --> 00:36:41,955
No, because I know who I am.

675
00:36:42,992 --> 00:36:45,996
I know how to be him.

676
00:36:49,791 --> 00:36:52,715
And you helped that. So, thank you.

677
00:36:53,628 --> 00:36:54,754
Ed.

678
00:36:56,756 --> 00:36:57,757
(CLEARS THROAT)

679
00:36:59,300 --> 00:37:01,598
- You killed six people.
- Mmm-hmm.

680
00:37:01,761 --> 00:37:03,763
Seven, including Penguin.

681
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:07,772
You just announced to the entire city
that you are a villain and a murderer.

682
00:37:08,184 --> 00:37:09,185
Mmm-hmm.

683
00:37:10,270 --> 00:37:14,867
Ed, if there is any part of your mind
that is not insane,

684
00:37:15,024 --> 00:37:16,025
listen to me.

685
00:37:18,987 --> 00:37:21,831
You need help. Turn yourself in.

686
00:37:26,119 --> 00:37:30,124
My actions seem mad to you.

687
00:37:32,667 --> 00:37:34,214
To anyone.

688
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:37,922
'Nu-

689
00:37:42,218 --> 00:37:47,099
I just killed
the best friend that I have ever had.

690
00:37:50,059 --> 00:37:53,563
My search for a teacher or an enemy,

691
00:37:56,608 --> 00:37:59,208
that was just me trying
to hold on to him for a little bit longer.

692
00:37:59,986 --> 00:38:01,909
But now I know who I am

693
00:38:03,948 --> 00:38:05,746
without him.

694
00:38:06,201 --> 00:38:07,453
So who are you now?

695
00:38:08,703 --> 00:38:10,797
Oh, come on, Foxy.

696
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:15,836
I'm The Riddler.

697
00:38:24,344 --> 00:38:26,017
(LAUGHING)

698
00:38:27,889 --> 00:38:29,516
(POLICE SIRENS BLARING IN DISTANCE)

699
00:38:37,106 --> 00:38:38,824
(SHIP HORN HONKING)

700
00:38:42,445 --> 00:38:44,038
I've always loved the view from here.

701
00:38:44,948 --> 00:38:47,747
Not really a fan. You understand why.

702
00:38:52,747 --> 00:38:55,147
I want you to know that our friendship
meant something to me.

703
00:38:57,418 --> 00:39:00,592
I cared about you, and I miss you.

704
00:39:02,924 --> 00:39:05,518
Gee. Almost makes up for being dead.

705
00:39:06,427 --> 00:39:08,771
You do know the entire GCPD
is hunting you.

706
00:39:10,098 --> 00:39:11,441
Yes.

707
00:39:12,976 --> 00:39:15,570
Well, not to burst your bubble,
but wanted or not,

708
00:39:15,728 --> 00:39:18,732
no one is going to be afraid
of "The Riddler."

709
00:39:20,525 --> 00:39:23,404
Maybe not yet, but they will be.

710
00:40:00,523 --> 00:40:02,150
Goodbye, Oswald.

711
00:40:20,543 --> 00:40:22,386
(GROANING AND GASPING)

712
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:28,180
Well, look who's alive.

713
00:40:29,177 --> 00:40:30,554
(GASPING)

714
00:40:31,054 --> 00:40:32,180
Who are you?

715
00:40:32,597 --> 00:40:34,315
Ivy Pepper, you stupid.

716
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:37,397
(GASPING)

717
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:38,903
Do we know each other?

718
00:40:39,062 --> 00:40:40,359
I pulled you out of the river.

719
00:40:41,606 --> 00:40:42,983
Been nursing you for weeks.

720
00:40:43,316 --> 00:40:46,069
So boring. You sleep a lot.

721
00:40:46,945 --> 00:40:47,946
(GROANS)

722
00:40:50,531 --> 00:40:54,081
You look strange, like you're gonna puke.
Are you okay?

723
00:41:01,584 --> 00:41:03,257
I just remembered.

724
00:41:04,128 --> 00:41:06,096
There's someone I need to kill.

725
00:41:16,557 --> 00:41:17,809
Uncle Frank?

726
00:41:43,084 --> 00:41:44,256
KATHRYN: How did he take it?

727
00:41:44,419 --> 00:41:46,092
His interest is piqued.

728
00:41:46,254 --> 00:41:48,052
But convincing him will take some time.

729
00:41:48,256 --> 00:41:50,179
We don't have time.

730
00:41:51,217 --> 00:41:52,890
I won't let you down, Kathryn.

731
00:41:53,386 --> 00:41:55,066
I assume things went smoothly on your end?

732
00:41:56,055 --> 00:41:57,602
The clone is in place.

733
00:41:58,433 --> 00:41:59,434
(EXHALES)

734
00:41:59,642 --> 00:42:01,440
What about Bruce Wayne?

735
00:42:03,229 --> 00:42:05,903
He should be waking up as we speak.

736
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:10,319
(SNIFFS)

737
00:42:15,116 --> 00:42:16,117
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

738
00:42:45,063 --> 00:42:47,111
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

739
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:29,273
English - SDH

